    "en": {
      "title": "What Japan will do for Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Japanese Finance Minister Shunichi Suzuki said it was important to bring together Sri Lanka's creditors to discuss Sri Lanka's debt problems and Tokyo would coordinate creditors, Reuters reported.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe told Reuters last month that Sri Lanka would ask Japan to invite major creditors to talks on restructuring bilateral debts, according to Reuters.",
        "The Japanese Foreign Minister had said last week that he had not negotiated with Sri Lanka regarding holding such a creditor meeting."
      ],
